AB  - In this paper, we present a distributed resource allocation mechanism in cognitive radio networks, based on a new coopetition methodology, which combines advantages of nodes' competition and cooperation. We postulate that this new method allows for fully distributed resource management between cognitive radio devices. The presented framework is generic, however, we consider it for the application in OFDMA networks. Coopetition takes the best from cooperative and competitive problem formulation, and provides the opportunity to control the balance between fairness and spectral efficiency (SE) of resource allocation. Simulation results confirm that coopetition allows for efficient resource utilization, and may be used practically in wireless cognitive networks.
